item.content:encoded:
Imagine a strange, tropical place that is almost inaccessible. Time appears to have stood still there. Species of animal and plant life not seen elsewhere on Earth, except in the fossil record, inhabit the place. The lakes heave with the shapes of huge grey bulks moving under the surface. The woods are places where chittering cries move about above your head, as powerful apes move swiftly in the canopy of leaves. Then, a tree splinters nearby, and a dinosaur steps out from his hiding place… and he’s eyeing YOU.

item.content:encoded:
Anthem is a dystopian fiction novella by Ayn Rand, written in 1937 and first published in 1938 in England. It takes place at some unspecified future date when mankind has entered another dark age characterized by irrationality, collectivism, and socialistic thinking and economics. Technological advancement is now carefully planned (when it is allowed to occur at all) and the concept of individuality has been eliminated (for example, the use of the word “I” is punishable by death).

item.title: New Adult Romance Recommendations
item.dc:creator: audiolibri.org
item.description: New Adult Romance is one of my favorite genres so I thought I would share a few recommendations with you today. It can be hard to find great books in this genre, but hre are some of my all time favorite books from the New Adult Romance genre. All of these books can be found …
item.content:encoded:
New Adult Romance is one of my favorite genres so I thought I would share a few recommendations with you today. It can be hard to find great books in this genre, but hre are some of my all time favorite books from the New Adult Romance genre. All of these books can be found on Amazon or The Book Depository. The full list of books mentioned in this video is just below.

Books mentioned:
Confess by Colleen Hoover
Maybe Someday by Colleen Hoover
November 9 by Colleen Hoover
Ugly Love by Colleen Hoover
It Ends With Us by Colleen Hoover
Before We Were Strangers by Renee Carlino
Swear On This Life by Renee Carlino
One True Loves by Taylor Jenkins Reid
Unteachable by Leah Raeder
Loving Mr. Daniels by Brittainy C. Cherry
The Air He Breathes by Brittainy C. Cherry
Come To Me Quietly by A.L. Jackson
Fade In by M. Mabie
He Will Be My Ruin by K.A. Tucker (thriller)
Sweet Filthy Boy by Christina Lauren
Wicked Sexy Liar by Christina Lauren
The Deal by Elle Kennedy
Him by Sarina Bowen and Elle Kennedy (M/M)

(More on the adult side, but reads like a New Adult)
Attachments by Rainbow Rowell
Maybe In Another Life by Taylor Jenkins Reid

Hope you enjoy these recommendations! Have you read any of these? What are your favorites out of all the books I meantioned? Do you have any NA Romance recommendations for me?
xoxo, Gabby
